[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 142/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_141 prediction="Let's break this down:\n\n1. We know there are 700 bees in total.\n2. Let's denote the number of baby bees as B, worker bees as W, and queen bees as Q.\n3. We are told that there are twice as many worker bees as baby bees, so W = 2B.\n4. We are also told that there are twice as many babies as queens, so B = 2Q.\n5. Since W = 2B, we can substitute B from the second equation into the first equation: W = 2(2Q) => W = 4Q.\n6. Now, we have two equations with two variables:\n   - B = 2Q\n   - W = 4Q\n7. We can solve these equations simultaneously to find the number of baby bees (B) and worker bees (W).\n8. From the first equation, we can express Q in terms of B: Q = B/2.\n9. Substitute Q from the first equation into the second equation: W = 4(B/2) => W = 2B.\n1" gold='400' correct=False
