[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 310/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_309 prediction="First, let's find out how many arms a person will grow in 15 days. Since a new arm is grown every three days, we divide the total number of days (15) by the number of days for one arm (3).\n\nNumber of arms = Total days / Days per arm\n= 15 / 3\n= 5 arms\n\nNext, let's find out how many legs a person will grow in 15 days. Since a new leg is grown every five days, we divide the total number of days (15) by the number of days for one leg (5).\n\nNumber of legs = Total days / Days per leg\n= 15 / 5\n= 3 legs\n\nSince a person has two legs initially, the total number of legs after 15 days will be the initial number of legs (2) plus the number of new legs (3).\n\nTotal legs = Initial legs + New legs\n= 2 + 3\n= 5 legs\n\nHowever, we need to account for the extra arm growth as well. Since each arm is attached to a torso, each arm also requires a leg. So, for every new arm" gold='8' correct=False
