[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 324/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_323 prediction="1. Shannon starts with an unknown amount of coffee. Let's denote the initial amount as C.\n2. For each ice cube she adds, the coffee gets weaker by 12 milliliters and cools by 13 degrees. So, the number of ice cubes (I) can be found by dividing the total cooling needed (65 degrees) by the cooling per ice cube (13 degrees), and then subtracting the 15 milliliters of cream she adds, because the cream does not affect the temperature but increases the volume: I = (65 - 15) / 13 = 4 + 12/13 ≈ 5.31 (approximately 5 ice cubes).\n3. Since each ice cube weakens the coffee by 12 milliliters, the total weakening due to ice cubes is 12 * 5 = 60 milliliters.\n4. However, the 15 milliliters of cream she adds will counteract some of the weakening caused by the ice cubes. To find the net weakening, subtract" gold='75' correct=False
