[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 326/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_325 prediction='1. We know that the total number of employees is 100.\n2. Junior programmers are 2/5 of the total number of employees, so there are 2/5 * 100 = 40 junior programmers.\n3. Senior programmers are the remaining employees, so there are 100 - 40 = 60 senior programmers.\n4. Junior programmers are paid $2000 per month, so they receive a total of 40 * $2000 = $80,000 per month.\n5. Senior programmers are paid $400 more than junior programmers, so they are paid $2000 + $400 = $2400 per month.\n6. The total amount of money the company pays to senior programmers is 60 * $2400 = $144,000 per month.\n7. To find the total amount of money the company pays to all the programmers per month, we add the amounts for junior and senior programmers: $80,000 + $144,000 = $2' gold='224000' correct=False
