[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 360/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_359 prediction="First, let's find out how many cents Billy has left after buying candy. Since each pound of candy costs $1.5, and he has $10, the number of pounds he can buy is $10 / $1.5 = 6.67 (rounded to two decimal places). However, since he can't buy a fraction of a pound, he can buy 6 pounds of candy.\n\nNext, let's find out how much change he has after buying candy. The change is the total amount he had ($10) minus the cost of the candy (6 * $1.5 = $9).\n\nThen, he takes half of his change and spends it on gumballs. Half of $9 is $4.5. Since gumballs cost $.05 each, he can buy 4.5 / .05 = 90 gumballs. But he only bought 40 gumballs, so he must have spent the other half of his change on something else.\n\nSince he didn't spend all his change on gumballs, he must have bought more than 6 pounds of candy. However, we" gold='4' correct=False
