[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 364/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_363 prediction="1. First, let's find out the time it took John to drive to his friend's house without the detour. Time = Distance / Speed, so it took him 200 miles / 70 mph = 2.86 hours (approximately).\n2. Next, we add the extra 10 miles from the detour, which takes an additional 10 miles / 70 mph = 0.14 hours (approximately).\n3. So, the total time to reach his friend's house is 2.86 hours + 0.14 hours = 3 hours and 52 minutes (approximately).\n4. On the way back, he drives 240 miles at 80 mph. Time = Distance / Speed, so it took him 240 miles / 80 mph = 3 hours.\n5. Since he didn't take any detour on the way back, the total time for the round trip is the sum of the time to reach his friend's house and the time to return home, which is 3 hours and 52 minutes (approximately" gold='6' correct=False
