[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 409/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_408 prediction="1. First, let's find out how many words Toby needs to read in total: Words_total = Pages * Words_per_page = 45 * 200 = 9000 words.\n2. Next, let's find out how many words Toby can read in 60 minutes: Words_in_60_minutes = Reading_rate * Minutes = 300 * 60 = 18000 words.\n3. Since Toby has 9000 words to read, we can find out how many minutes it will take him to read the book: Minutes_to_read = Words_to_read / Reading_rate = 9000 / 300 = 30 minutes.\n4. Now, we subtract the time it takes to get to the airport (10 minutes) from the time it takes to read the book (30 minutes): Difference = Time_to_read - Time_to_get_to_airport = 30 - 10 = 20 minutes.\n5. Since Toby plans to leave as soon" gold='20' correct=False
