[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 555/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_554 prediction="Let's denote the time it takes Ray to swim a mile in cold water as C (minutes). In warm water, it takes him 2 minutes more than twice as long, so we can represent this as W = 2C + 2 (minutes).\n\nWe know that C + W = 16 (since the total time for swimming a mile in cold water is 16 minutes) and W + W + W = 3W (since the total time for swimming 3 miles in warm water is 3 times the time for a single mile).\n\nNow we can solve the system of equations:\n\n1) C + W = 16\n2) 3W = W + W + W\n\nSubstitute W from equation 1 into equation 2:\n\n3) 3(16 - C) = 3W\n\nSince W = 2C + 2, we can substitute W in the above equation:\n\n3) 3(16 - C) = 3(2C + 2)\n\nSolve for C:\n\n24 - 3C = 6C + 6\n9C = 1" gold='54' correct=False
