[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 688/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_687 prediction="Let's denote the age of the older twin as T, the age of the younger twin as W, and the ages of the three triplets as A, B, and C, where A is the oldest among the triplets.\n\nWe know that T is 7 years older than one of the triplets, so T = A + 7.\nWe also know that W = A, because they are twins.\nThe sum of their ages is 44, so T + W + A + B + C = 44.\nSince W = A, we can rewrite the equation as T + 2A + B + C = 44.\n\nWe know that A, B, and C are triplets, so their ages are equal. Let's denote their common age as X. Then, B = C = X.\n\nSubstituting B and C into the equation, we get T + 2A + X + X + X = 44.\nSince T = A + 7, we can substitute T into the equation, getting (A + 7) + 2A + X + X + X = 44.\n\nSimplifying" gold='13' correct=False
