[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 878/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_877 prediction="Let's break this down:\n\n1. Isaias wants to sell 3/5 of his chickens to make a profit of $2000.\n2. He has 300 chickens in total. So, the number of chickens he wants to sell is 300 * (3/5) = 180 chickens.\n3. Let's assume he sells all these 180 chickens at $50 each. The total revenue from selling these chickens would be 180 * $50 = $9000.\n4. Since Isaias wants to make a profit of $2000, the cost price of the chickens he sold would be $9000 - $2000 = $7000.\n5. However, we don't know how many chickens he bought at this cost price. To find that out, we need to know how many of the 300 chickens he didn't sell.\n6. Isaias didn't sell 300 - 180 = 120 chickens.\n7. We don'" gold='7000' correct=False
