[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 939/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_938 prediction="1. John earns 50 dollars per hour and works for 6 hours, so he earns 50 * 6 = 300 dollars in total.\n2. He spends 50 dollars on gas, leaving him with 300 - 50 = 250 dollars.\n3. He spends 10 dollars on pencils, leaving him with 250 - 10 = 240 dollars.\n4. A 25 dollar pen costs 25 dollars.\n5. To find out how many pens he can buy, we divide the remaining money by the cost of each pen: 240 / 25 = 9.6. Since he can't buy a fraction of a pen, he can buy 9 pens.\n6. After buying 5 pencils and 9 pens, he has spent 10 + (9 * 25) = 10 + 225 = 235 dollars.\n7. He still has 235 - 300 = -65 dollars, which means he doesn't have enough money to buy any more pens." gold='4' correct=False
