[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 1001/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_1000 prediction="First, let's calculate the time Doctor Jones spends on rounds. He has 9 inpatients, and each round takes 20 minutes. So, the total time for rounds is 9 * 20 = 180 minutes.\n\nNext, let's calculate the time for appointments. He has 10 appointments, and each appointment takes 30 minutes. So, the total time for appointments is 10 * 30 = 300 minutes.\n\nNow, let's add the time for rounds and appointments to find the total time Doctor Jones spends on these activities. Total time = 180 (rounds) + 300 (appointments) = 480 minutes.\n\nSince there are 60 minutes in an hour, we can convert the total time to hours: 480 minutes / 60 minutes/hour = 8 hours.\n\nDoctor Jones works for 9 hours at the clinic, and he has already spent 8 hours on rounds and appointments. So, he has 9 (total hours) - 8 (spent hours) = 1 hour left to update his records" gold='1' correct=False
