[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 1048/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_1047 prediction="Let's denote the number of balls Rory retrieved in the first, second, and third sets as F, S, and T respectively.\n\nWe know that F > S and T = 0.5 * S.\nAlso, we know that the total number of balls retrieved is 19, so F + S + T = 19.\n\nSubstitute T with 0.5 * S in the equation:\nF + S + 0.5 * S = 19\n\nCombine the terms:\n1.5 * S = 19 - S\n\nNow, solve for S:\n1.5 * S - S = 19\n0.5 * S = 19\nS = 19 / 0.5\nS = 38\n\nSince we know that F > S, F cannot be 38. So, let's find the number of balls Rory retrieved in the first set by subtracting the number of balls he retrieved in the second set from the total number of balls he retrieved:\n\nF = 19 - S = 19 - 38 = -1" gold='10' correct=False
