[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 1078/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_1077 prediction="1. The first train arrives in 10 minutes and stays for 20 minutes, so it will be at the station for a total of 30 minutes.\n2. The second train leaves 30 + 30/2 (since it's half an hour after the first train leaves) = 60 minutes after the first train departs. It stays for a quarter of the time the first train stayed, which is 20 minutes / 4 = 5 minutes.\n3. The third train leaves an hour after the second train, so it leaves at 60 + 60 = 120 minutes after the first train departs. It stays for the same amount of time as the second train, so it will be at the station for 5 minutes.\n4. The fourth train leaves 20 minutes after the third train, so it leaves at 120 + 20 = 140 minutes after the first train departs.\n5. Paul boards the fourth train, so he waits for a total of 140 minutes - the time the first train departed, which is 140 - 10 = 130 minutes" gold='145' correct=False
