[zero_shot][mistral_7b_instruct_v0_3][gsm8k] sample 1148/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_1147 prediction='To find out how many days it takes for Lauren to complete the project, we first need to determine how many picture scenes she can draw in one day in total.\n\n1. For large-sized scenes, she can draw 5 scenes per day.\n2. For medium-sized scenes, she can draw 6 scenes per day.\n3. For small-sized scenes, she can draw 7 scenes per day.\n\nTo find the total number of scenes she can draw in one day, we add the number of scenes she can draw for each size:\n\nTotal scenes per day = Large + Medium + Small\nTotal scenes per day = 5 + 6 + 7 = 18 scenes per day\n\nNow, we need to find out how many days it takes to complete all the picture scenes:\n\n1. For large-sized scenes, she needs to draw 45 scenes.\n2. For medium-sized scenes, she needs to draw 36 scenes.\n3. For small-sized scenes, she needs to draw 49 scenes.\n\nTo find the total number of days needed, we divide the total number of scenes for each size by the number of scenes she can draw' gold='22' correct=False
